# {{ project_name }}

> An Obsidian vault for creative worldbuilding, generated by [Grimoire](https://github.com/niklastypes/grimoire).

## Vault Structure

This vault uses the **three-layer model**:

| Layer | Purpose | Folders |
|---|---|---|
| **1. Canon** | The universe: entities, lore, source material | `world/`{% if include_sources %}, `sources/`{% endif %} |
| **2. Creative** | What you build on canon: plot, systems | `story/`{% if project_type != 'generic' %}, `mechanics/`{% endif %} |
{% if project_type == 'ttrpg' %}| **3. Production** | What you bring to the table | `play/` |
{% endif %}
### Supporting Folders

- `templates/` — note templates (use Obsidian's Insert Template)
- `views/` — Bases view definitions
- `assets/` — images, audio, media

## Properties

All notes use frontmatter properties. Key properties:

| Property | Values | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `type` | `character`, `location`, `item`, `faction`, `lore`, `scene`{% if project_type == 'ttrpg' %}, `session-prep`, `session-log`, `encounter`{% endif %} | Note type identifier |
| `status` | `draft`, `ready`, `revealed`, `retired` | Content lifecycle |
| `canon` | `true` / `false` | Is this canonical to the universe? |
| `source` | string | Attribution (e.g., "self", "Hillenbrand 2018") |
| `genai` | `true` / `false` | AI-generated content flag |

## Conventions

- **Naming:** lowercase kebab-case for all files and folders
- **Templates:** one per note type in `templates/`, flat (no subfolders)
- **Views:** Bases `.base` files in `views/`
- **Dashboard:** `home.md` is the vault entry point
- **New notes:** always use a template; place entities in `world/`, scenes in `story/`{% if project_type == 'ttrpg' %}, session notes in `play/`{% endif %}

## Working With This Vault

- Read `home.md` first for an overview
- Use existing templates when creating notes
- Set `canon: false` for non-canonical content (homebrew, what-if scenarios)
- Set `genai: true` on any AI-generated content
- Keep `world/` flat (no subfolders), use properties and links for organization
